line_1: Pursue the hare, or chace the miscreant fox
line_2: With winged speed o'er hills or craggy rocks.

line_1: Ne Judge unjust, with furred Fox,
line_2: Harming in Secret Guise the Flocks:

line_1: The quiet harmless Posture of the Fox.
line_2: Perch'd on her Bough the wanton Chirper mocks

line_1: Let them rail at the fruit they can't reach, like the fox,
line_2: While I have the lass with the golden locks.

line_1: Nay then, replys the feeble Fox,
line_2: (But, hark! I hear a hen that clocks)
May taunt you wi' his jeers an' mocks;
But gie him't het, my hearty cocks!
An' send him to his dicing box,
